                <head>No. 82.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Cadwalader</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Davis</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1876-05-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 31, 1876</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 237.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your No. 358, of the 1st instant,
                    relative to the National Evangelical Church of Germany, I have to state that the
                    report <pb facs="0205" n="149" xml:id="pg_149"/> of Mr. Chapman Coleman
                    respecting the laws regulating that organization and the proposed changes
                    therein, which accompanied your dispatch, exhibits an intelligent investigation
                    which is deserving of commendation.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JOHN L. CADWALADER,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
